# Authors

## Original authors

Nikhil K. Harle
Bo-Yu Chen
Bob Bao
Hannes Bernien

These authors created the core atommovr framework, including the algorithm
base class, error model base class, move utilities, AtomArray, and the initial
benchmark infrastructure.

## Additional contributions

Sascha Benz
Ludwig-Maximilians-Universitaet Muenchen, Ryd-Yb tweezer array group
2025-2026
Imaging pipeline, PCFA rearrangement algorithm, Tetris rearrangement algorithm,  AWG controller for Spectrum Instrumentation M4i.6631-x8 cards with DDS cores: RFConverter, AWGBatch, AODSettings, RFRamp, and core-assignment logic,  DDS execution strategies: ramp, pattern, and camera-triggered modes, atommovr production controller, Benchmark and analysis scripts (run_rearranging_benchmarks.py and extension of benchmarking.py), Demonstration scripts (demo_awg_control.py, demo_pipeline.py, imaging_demo.py), Image scaling and blob parameter optimisation scripts, Test suite extensions (test_awg_control.py, test_controller_pipeline.py, test_imaging.py additions)

## Third-party code and attributions

### slmsuite

Portions of `atommovr/utils/imaging/extraction.py` (the Extractor class and
related extraction helpers) were adapted from the slmsuite project.

  Project:   slmsuite
  Authors:   slmsuite Developers (2021-2025)
  License:   MIT
  Source:    https://github.com/slmsuite/slmsuite

The original MIT license and copyright notice are preserved in the source file
header. Modifications made during adaptation are covered by this repository's
MIT license.

### spcm (Spectrum Instrumentation Python SDK)

The AWG controller and DDS strategy modules use the `spcm` Python package,
which is the official Python SDK for Spectrum Instrumentation hardware.

  Product:   spcm Python package
  Vendor:    Spectrum Instrumentation GmbH
  Source:    https://github.com/SpectrumInstrumentation/spcm
             https://pypi.org/project/spcm/
  License:   MIT (as of spcm >= 0.4)

The spcm package is a dependency of this project and is not redistributed
within the repository. Its copyright and license terms apply independently
when installed.
